Magic in the garden

This is my first time messing with AI in photoshop's latest update. It does some incredible things and the industry is changed forever. 

This was an image I had on the back burner for some time simply because I wasn't sure how I was going to add glowing flowers. But once I gave AI a shot, it did it with little issue.

I used "glowing flowers" and "change clothes" prompt to get the result.

Is it amazing? It is. Is it perfect? No, but it's getting closer and closer. Do I support ai art? Absolutely the hell not. I hate it. It's soulless and takes the fun out of the process. It shouldn't exist. But it does, and there's nothing we can do about it but learn to work with it or get left behind

Shot on my a7iii / 50mm 1.4 and edited in Adobe Photoshop 👨🏻‍💻
